{"type":"message","id":"a2d26fea","parentId":"ef83c92e","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:10:49.406Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_0l8nhh71oq7l_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 080821\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n2. There's a pending TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment\r\n3. Next action is to implement TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n\r\nThe current phase advancement is about COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY, which unifies Phase 1 and Phase 2.\r\n\r\nThe immediate next action should be:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist in the sandbox to understand the current state. I should look at the logs directory and any existing pulse files to understand the format.\r\n\r\nThe most logical next action is to start implementing the TIC experiment. I need to:\r\n1. Look at the existing pulse logs to understand their format\r\n2. Create a TIC classifier that analyzes pulse content for invariants vs variants\r\n3. Test on the last 20 pulse logs\r\n\r\nLet me start by examining what logs exist and their format.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC Experiment is the critical next step to validate the Compression-Causal Duality hypothesis. I need to first examine the structure of existing pulse logs to understand what patterns constitute invariants vs variants, then implement the classifier.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nExamine recent pulse logs to understand their structure and content patterns, then create a TIC classifier prototype that identifies invariant vs variant content across sessions.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCausal structure IS invariant structure — compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\n## Methodology\r\n1. Parse last 20 pulse logs\r\n2. Extract content tokens (goals, actions, insights, file references)\r\n3. Classify each token as INVARIANT (recurs across sessions) or VARIANT (session-specific)\r\n4. Predict next pulse content from invariant set\r\n5. Measure accuracy against success criteria\r\n\r\n## Success Criteria\r\n- Invariant/variant classification: >70% accuracy\r\n- Next-pulse prediction: >60% accuracy\r\n\r\n## Log Analysis\r\n\r\n### Pulse Log Format\r\nEach pulse log contains:\r\n- Observation (1-2 sentences)\r\n- Action (file edit description)\r\n- Mutation (old/new text pairs)\r\n\r\n### Token Extraction\r\n```\r\nINVARIANT patterns:\r\n- Goal statements (\"Phase X\", \"COMPLETE\", \"PENDING\")\r\n- Framework references (\"TemporalAttention\", \"Breakaway\", \"Infant\")\r\n- Structural phrases (\"Last updated:\", \"###\")\r\n\r\nVARIANT patterns:\r\n- Timestamps (\"2026-03-24 080517\")\r\n- Specific file paths (logs/pulse_*.md)\r\n- Content-specific observations\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Next: Implement classifier and run on logs/\r\nfile: research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 08:08:42\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774354249403}}
